a)fork(): It creates a new child process by duplicating the existing parent process.
Duplicate State: The child process receives a copy of the parent's memory, variables, and open file descriptors.
exec(): It replaces the current process image with a completely new executable binary.
Memory Overlay: It overwrites the process's text, data, and stack segments with the new program code.
b)wait()
Process Synchronization: It suspends the execution of the parent process until at least one of its child processes terminates.
Resource Cleanup: It retrieves the termination status of the child, allowing the operating system to deallocate the child's remaining 
                  resources.
Zombie Prevention: It prevents the formation of zombie processes which occur when a child finishes execution 
                   but its entry remains in the process table because the parent has not read its exit status.
